While the Internet Archive&#39;s crawls most often get all media types, so 
that pages can be realistically redisplayed at a later date, one of the 
most commonly asked questions is &quot;how can I use Heritrix for crawling 
only HTML and other textual formats?&quot;

So, I think your pre-download type-predictive work would be of keen 
interest to the overall community. Please keep the list apprised of your 
progress of of any code that&#39;s available for integration to the main 
Heritrix distribution.

- Gordon @ IA

